      "posts": [
        {
          "id": "post1",
          "title": "What is The Trial really about?",
          "content": "Kafka's The Trial explores absurdity and bureaucracy...",
          "authorName": "Alice",
          "createdAt": "2h ago",
          "user_id": "user_1",
          "upvotes": 142,
          "comment_count": 45,
          "comments": [
            {
              "comment_id": "c1_p1_1",
              "post_id": "post1",
              "user_id": "user_2",
              "content": "I think it is a direct critique of the Austro-Hungarian legal system of his time. The labyrinthine bureaucracy is the real antagonist.",
              "authorName": "Bob",
              "createdAt": "1h ago",
              "upvotes": 34
            },
            {
              "comment_id": "c1_p1_2",
              "post_id": "post1",
              "user_id": "user_3",
              "content": "That makes sense historically, but the surrealism points to something deeper, like existential guilt. The court isn't a real place, it's his conscience.",
              "authorName": "Charlie",
              "createdAt": "45m ago",
              "upvotes": 21
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "post2",
          "title": "Kafka's symbolism explained",
          "content": "Many readers interpret Kafka's work as existential literature...",
          "authorName": "Bob",
          "createdAt": "5h ago",
          "user_id": "user_2",
          "upvotes": 89,
          "comment_count": 23,
          "comments": [
            {
              "comment_id": "c1_p2_1",
              "post_id": "post2",
              "user_id": "user_1",
              "content": "The beetle in The Metamorphosis is such a powerful symbol of alienation and self-loathing.",
              "authorName": "Alice",
              "createdAt": "4h ago",
              "upvotes": 18
            },
            {
              "comment_id": "c1_p2_2",
              "post_id": "post2",
              "user_id": "user_3",
              "content": "I always saw the doors and corridors as representing the futility of modern life.",
              "authorName": "Charlie",
              "createdAt": "3h ago",
              "upvotes": 12
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
