        {
          "id": "post_dark_matter",
          "title": "Is Dark Matter just a placeholder?",
          "content": "Exploring MOND as an alternative to the dark matter hypothesis...",
          "authorName": "Dr. Sarah",
          "createdAt": "45m ago",
          "user_id": "user_1",
          "upvotes": 67,
          "comment_count": 18,
          "comments": [
            {
              "comment_id": "c2_dm_1",
              "post_id": "post_dark_matter",
              "user_id": "user_2",
              "content": "MOND works well for galaxy rotation curves but fails at cluster scales. Dark matter is still the best framework we have.",
              "authorName": "Neil",
              "createdAt": "30m ago",
              "upvotes": 15
            },
            {
              "comment_id": "c2_dm_2",
              "post_id": "post_dark_matter",
              "user_id": "user_3",
              "content": "What about the bullet cluster? That's pretty hard evidence for dark matter being a real substance.",
              "authorName": "Buzz",
              "createdAt": "20m ago",
              "upvotes": 9
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "post_spacetime",
          "title": "Visualizing 4D Spacetime",
          "content": "Why the rubber sheet analogy fails us and how to better conceptualize gravity...",
          "authorName": "Buzz",
          "createdAt": "3h ago",
          "user_id": "user_1",
          "upvotes": 54,
          "comment_count": 12,
          "comments": [
            {
              "comment_id": "c2_st_1",
              "post_id": "post_spacetime",
              "user_id": "user_1",
              "content": "I think the best visualization is actually the embedding diagrams from Misner, Thorne, and Wheeler.",
              "authorName": "Dr. Sarah",
              "createdAt": "2h ago",
              "upvotes": 11
            },
            {
              "comment_id": "c2_st_2",
              "post_id": "post_spacetime",
              "user_id": "user_2",
              "content": "The rubber sheet analogy is circular - it uses gravity to explain gravity!",
              "authorName": "Neil",
              "createdAt": "1h ago",
              "upvotes": 7
            }
          ]
        }
